projects.description:
Because of mistakes and a lack of knowledge, the Active Directory of the Windows 2003 domain was damaged and corrupted. They decided to setup a new Windows 2003 domain.
Anton was responsible for the implementation of the new Windows 2003 domain. This project also included a new installation of Exchange 2003 and the integration of the existing Citrix Presentation Server farm with the new domain. After finishing the implementation, all user accounts had to be migrated to the new infrastructure.

My responsibilities include:
•	Designing and implementing Windows 2003 domain;
•	Installing and configuring Windows 2003 servers;
•	Installing and configuring Exchange 2003 server;
•	Adjusting Citrix Presentation Server 4.0 farm for integration with the new domain;
•	Migrating user accounts and mailboxes;
•	Assisting the local administrators;
•	Documenting the IT infrastructure.

Vereniging Natuurmonumenten is a non-profit organisation for protection of the natural environment. Following the development and roll out of the Citrix XenApp based user workspace, the project for development of the FAT-client started. The FAT-client was meant for the regional offices as well as the head office. To take full advantage of new technologies this, so called, FAT-client was based on Windows 8.1 combined with AppSense DesktopNow suite to manage the user workspace.
Anton was charged with the implementation and configuration of the AppSense DesktopNow suite. He also took part in the transition of applications to the new Windows 8.1 platform.
The IT infrastructure of Vereniging Natuurmonumenten is not only used by this organization. Several other organizations for protection of the natural environment obtain IT services from Vereniging Natuurmonumenten. These organizations are completely integrated in the IT infrastructure. The project team was in charge migrating the applications and user account of these organizations too.
After a period of developing, building and extensive testing the project team migrated the user accounts of the branch offices and the head office to the new user workspace. 

My responsibilities include:
•	Installation and configuration of AppSense DesktopNow suite (8.4/8.5);
•	Application transition to Windows 8.1;
•	User account migration from Windows XP/2003 to Windows 8/2008 with XenApp 6.5 user workspace and Windows 8.1;
•	Investigating and solving incidents and problems.

Because of the forthcoming end-of-life date for Windows XP the IT department started a project to develop a new IT infrastructure for the end users. At first, they decided to develop a Windows 7/2008 infrastructure combined with Citrix XenApp 6.5 and AppSense suite. In the end, Windows 7 was replaced by Windows 8 as client operating system. In this phase the project was focused at the development of the XenApp user workspace for all the branch offices. 
Anton was a member of the project team and was responsible for  the installation and configuration of the XenApp servers as well as the installation and configuration of AppSense suite to manage the user workspace. After a period of developing, building and extensive testing, the project team migrated the user accounts of the branch offices to the new user workspace.

My responsibilities include:
•	Installation and configuration of AppSense DesktopNow suite (8.3/8.4);
•	Developing scripted XenApp 6.5 installation;
•	Installation and configuration of the Citrix XenApp 6.5 farm;
•	User account migration from Windows XP/2003 to Windows 8/2008 with XenApp 6.5 user workspace;
•	Investigating and solving incidents and problems.

The IT department bought AppSense suite in 2010. They wanted to implement the software themselves. However, because of a lack of time and knowledge they decided to hire a third party to implement AppSense suite.
Anton was responsible for the AppSense implementation in the existing Windows 2003/XP IT infrastructure. The main goals of the AppSense implementation were to replace the roaming profiles with the AppSense User Virtualization solution and to replace the login script with the AppSense Environment Manager policy. 
Anton implemented User Virtualization/Personalization and converted the login script to an Environment Manager policy. After a period of testing, AppSense suite has been implemented in the production IT infrastructure.

My responsibilities include:
•	Installation and implementation AppSense Suite (8.2/8.3);
•	Migrating roaming profiles to AppSense User Virtualization/Personalization;
•	Handing over the AppSense administration to the IT department;
•	Investigating and solving incidents and problems.

The project ‘Pygmalion III’ concerned the implementation of a new IT infrastructure for the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
Anton was a member of the projects roll out team. The team was responsible for rolling out the new infrastructure at all Dutch embassies and consulates. At all locations abroad, the team renewed all components of the local IT infrastructure (routers, switches, servers, etc.). When the installation of the hardware was finished, all user accounts, mailboxes and data had to be migrated to the new IT infrastructure.

My responsibilities include:
•	Installing new networking components;
•	Installing new server en MSA storage device;
•	Migrating data, mailboxes and databases;
•	Migrating client/server applications;
•	Investigating and solving incidents and problems.

Anton participated in several projects and was a member of the Wintel administration team. Besides these roles, he was the lead system engineer for an IBM customer with business in the financial sector.

Projects/tasks:
•	Optimisation of a Windows 2003 infrastructure with Citrix Presentation Server 4.0 for a customer with business in the financial sector. This organisation was based in Amsterdam with branch offices in Stockholm and London.
•	Implementation of a new Windows 2003 infrastructure combined with Citrix Presentation Server 4.0 for a customer with business in transport/logistics.
•	Upgrading several internal IBM systems to Windows 2008.
•	Security compliance project for a large customer with business in construction.

My responsibilities include:
•	Administer Microsoft Windows 2003/2008 networks;
•	Installing and configuring Windows 2003/2008 servers;
•	Installing and configuring Citrix Presentation Server farms;
•	Advising and assisting with application migration tasks;
•	Producing documentation;
•	Producing and maintain procedures;
•	Investigating and solving incidents and problems;
•	Preparing and implementing changes;
•	Advising the customer, as the lead system engineer, about maintaining and improving the IT infrastructure.

Vitens is a water company providing drinking water.
Anton was a member of the IT administration team in Utrecht. He took part in day to day system administration as well as running and upcoming projects.

My responsibilities include:
•	Administering the Microsoft Windows 2003 network;
•	Installing Windows 2003 servers;
•	Assisting application administrators by application installation and troubleshooting;
•	Documenting newly installed products and solutions;
•	Assisting the first-line and second-line support teams;
•	Producing and maintaining procedures;
•	Investigating and solving incidents and problems.

The department ICTRO of the Ministry of Justice provides IT services to the all the courts in the Netherlands.
Anton was a member of a project team responsible for the implementation ReIS (justice information system). The implementation was phased according to the DTAP model. 

My responsibilities include:
•	Delivering software versions and manuals for packaging;
•	Testing the application versions at a technical level;
•	Producing and maintain documentation;
•	Assisting the forthcoming application administrators.

VolkerRail is a construction company with a focus on railway systems. It consisted of 16 locations and 15 branch offices.
Anton was a member of the IT administration team. This team was responsible for the administration and maintenance of the central IT infrastructure. The infrastructure was based on Windows 2000 as well as Windows 2003. It contained a Citrix Presentation Server 4.0 farm and the user workspace was managed with RES PowerFuse.

My responsibilities include:
•	Administering the Windows 2000/2003 network;
•	Installing and configuring Windows 2000/2003 servers;
•	Administering the Exchange 2003 environment;
•	Assisting the application administrators;
•	Producing and maintaining procedures;
•	Investigating and solving incidents and problems.

The IT administration organization of Rabobank International was divided among two locations, Utrecht and London. The organisation was responsible for the administration of the central IT infrastructure for all Rabobank offices abroad. The IT infrastructure was spread over four data centres, three in The Netherlands and one in the United Kingdom. To facilitate the office abroad, the infrastructure contained a Citrix Metaframe XP farm. Anton was a member of the IT administration team in Utrecht.

My responsibilities include:
•	Monitoring the infrastructure with SIM en MOM;
•	Administering the Microsoft Windows 2003 network;
•	Installing and configuring Windows 2003 servers;
•	Assisting the application administrators;
•	Documenting newly implemented products;
•	Producing and maintaining procedures;
•	Investigating and solving incidents and problems.

Rabofacet was a subsidiary of Rabobank Nederland, dedicated to delivering facilities to all local bank offices.
Anton was a member of the central IT administration team based in Zeist. The team was charged with the administration of the IT infrastructure of all local bank offices in The Netherlands. Each local office had its own local administrator acting as a first point of contact. Besides the local administrator, each local office was assigned to one of five regional IT administration facilities for second-line support. The central team in Zeist was responsible for overall IT administration and third-line support.
The IT infrastructure was a mixed environment consisting of a Windows NT 4.0 domain with Windows 95 clients as well as a Windows 2000 domain with Windows XP clients.

My responsibilities include:
•	Administration and support for 400 local bank offices and 5 regional administration offices;
•	Windows NT 4.0 administration;
•	Windows 2000 administration;
•	Investigating and solving incidents and problems;
•	Producing reports, procedures and manuals;
•	Third-line support.

Milieudienst RZHZ is a governmental organization charged with environmental services.
Anton was a member of the project team that was responsible for the implementing a new IT infrastructure. This infrastructure was Windows 2003 based combined with Citrix MetaFrame and Windows XP. AppSense was also part of the implementation to manage and personalise the user workspace.

My responsibilities include:
•	Migrating user accounts, data and mailboxes;
•	Administering Windows 2003 network;
•	Administering Exchange 2003 environment;
•	Rolling out Windows XP clients;
•	Documenting the newly implemented IT infrastructure;
•	Investigating and solving incidents and problems.
